item.description:
So you need to configure pfSense with an UPS!? Well, good thing this post is called &ldquo;How to Setup UPS on pfSense&rdquo;.
a. Start by plugging the USB cable to your pfSense and your UPS
b. Now log in to the pfSense UI and go into &ldquo;System =&gt; Package Manager&rdquo;
b. Search for &lsquo;nut&rsquo; and click on &lsquo;Install&rsquo;
c. Go to &ldquo;Services =&gt; UPS =&gt; UPS Settings&rdquo;, select &ldquo;Local USB&rdquo;, give the UPS a name and click on &ldquo;Save&rdquo;
